      "caption": "This is what happens when live jazz and electronic music collide\n\nTakuya Nakamura is one of the most innovative performers in electronic music, blending jazz, jungle, ambient, and club sounds into a unique live experience that pushes the boundaries of a traditional DJ set.\n\nOriginally from Tokyo and now based in New York City, Nakamura has spent decades shaping the underground electronic music scene, turning every performance into a real-time fusion of live instruments and dancefloor energy.\n\nKnown for playing trumpet, keys, and synthesizers while DJing, he creates a sound that sits between jazz improvisation and modern electronic music culture.\n\nFrom studying under jazz pioneer George Russell to collaborating with legends like Quincy Jones, his work proves that live musicianship and club music can exist on the same stage.\n\nThis is not just a DJ set but a pure live performance."
