      "caption": "Werner Koch’s work on GnuPG became a quiet part of internet security because it gave people a free way to use strong encryption outside corporate control.\n\nGnuPG follows the OpenPGP standard, which helps users encrypt messages, verify files, sign software releases, and check whether downloads were tampered with.\n\nThe strange part is not that the project mattered, but that such important security work survived for years with very little funding and almost no public attention."
