      "caption": "Bad Film (2012)\nDir. Sion Sono\nIs an experimental movie set in Tokyo in 1997, depicting a violent conflict between Japanese and Chinese gangs in the Koenji district. Amidst the chaos and racial hatred, a Japanese boy and a Chinese girl fall in love and struggle to protect their relationship. Originally shot in 1995 with hundreds of amateur actors from Sono’s art collective Tokyo GAGAGA, the film was finally completed in 2012 using over 150 hours of raw video footage. Blending punk aesthetics, documentary style, and social commentary, it explores violence, identity, and love in a divided society.\nC: vijaunn\n*\n#badfilm #sionsono #punkcinema #experimentalfilm #undergroundvibes #cultmovie #fyp #foryou #explore #film #explorepage #japan"
