      "caption": "Calculating the surface area of a sphere through spatial equabilities.\nㅤ\nThe surface area of a sphere is given by the formula: Area = 4πr²\nㅤ\nWhere r is the radius of the sphere.\n ㅤ\nThis formula was discovered over two thousand years ago by the Greek philosopher Archemedes. He also realized that the surface area of ​​a sphere is equivalent to 2/3 of the surface area of ​​the smallest cylinder that can contain the sphere, and exactly equal to the area of ​​the curved wall of that cylinder.\nㅤ\nIf you know the surface area you can rearrange the formula above, finding the radius: r=√a/4π where a is the surface area.\nㅤ\n• Interesting facts\nㅤ\nFor a given volume, the sphere is the shape that has the smallest surface area. This why it appears in nature so much, such as water drops, bubbles and planets.\nㅤ\nThe surface area of a sphere is exactly four times the area of a circle with the same radius. You can see this in the area formula, since the area of a circle is πr² and the surface area of a sphere is 4πr².\nㅤ\n#FractalScience #SineWave #Graphic #PolarGraph #SurfaceAreaOfSphere #Sphere #Surface #Calculation #Volume #Measurement #Mathematics #Geometry #Science #Knowledge #Consciousness #Electromagnetism #Efficiency #Shape #Patterns #Cosmos #MusicOfTheSpheres #Harmony #Roundness #Balance #Energy #Vibration #Frequency #Fractal #Universe"
