      "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DZSkDrBkhl2/",
      "caption": "A founder shared what happened after processing more than 1.15 billion AI tokens in a single month, and most of the lessons had nothing to do with model quality.\n\nCosts increased mainly because of small decisions that seemed harmless on their own. Large JSON payloads, long prompts, unnecessary verbosity, and weak caching setups all quietly stacked up into significant spend over time.\n\nOutput tokens ended up being the biggest driver of cost. The longer the model response, the faster the bill grows, which makes generation length more important than most teams initially expect.\n\nAt that scale, AI stops being just a model choice and becomes an efficiency problem. Control over what gets sent, what gets generated, and how often calls are made starts to matter as much as the intelligence of the system itself.\n\nCredit: r/ClaudeAI\n\n➡️ Tech founder looking for traction?\n\nDM us “Market” to get your startup in front of 421k+ founders and operators."
